# Azveria Online - Player Guide

This guide explains how to use the site as a player and what each major section does.

## 1) Login and Account Creation

1. Open the website in your browser.
2. Create an account from the login page.
3. After registration, your player account is automatically linked to a new Nation.
4. Your Nation starts with default base resources, refined resources, currencies, and terrain square miles.

Note for admins:
- The default values for new players are configurable in the New Accounts tab.

## 2) Main Navigation

Player navigation includes:
- Player
- Announcements
- Map
- Chat
- Other Nations
- Shop
- Settings

Admin navigation includes:
- Announcements
- All Nations
- New Accounts
- Map
- Chat
- Shop

## 3) Player Tab

The Player tab shows:
- Nation identity (name, leader, alliance)
- Terrain square miles by type
- Expandable Base Resources
- Expandable Refined Resources grouped by type
- Expandable Currencies
- Units owned/training
- Buildings built/in progress

You can edit and save your Nation About text from this tab.

## 4) Announcements

- Players can read announcements.
- Admins can post announcements.

## 5) Map

Map features:
- Select map layers from the layer list.
- Mouse wheel zoom in and out.
- Click-drag to pan while zoomed.
- Reset View button appears when view is moved or zoomed.

Admin map features:
- Upload Main, Terrain, or Political layer images.

## 6) Chat

Chat features:
- Current chat name is shown in the header.
- Sent and received messages are visually distinct.
- Sender names are color-differentiated.
- Create group chats and add members.

## 7) Other Nations

Use this section to:
- Search nations by nation name or player name.
- View another nation's public overview (leader, alliance, about).

## 8) Shop

Player actions:
- Browse categories.
- Buy items.

Admin actions:
- Edit item costs with structured resource/currency selectors.
- Set item visibility globally or per-player.

Shop item effects can modify:
- Base resources
- Refined resources
- Currencies
- Units

## 9) Settings

Available settings:
- Theme (Light/Dark)
- Color blind mode
- Dog bark sound toggle

## 10) Help Menu

Help menu options:
- About: shows website version, game version, and admin name.
- Documentation: opens READMEPLAYER.
- Logout: signs out and returns to login page.

## 11) Admin: All Nations

Admin can:
- Create placeholder nations
- Edit nation identity fields
- Edit base resources
- Edit refined resources
- Edit currencies
- Add units to nations

## 12) Admin: New Accounts

Admin can configure defaults applied at account registration:
- Nation/leader naming templates
- Alliance/about defaults
- Base resources
- Refined resources (expandable groups)
- Currencies
- Terrain percentages
- Terrain square miles

These defaults are stored and reused for all new player registrations.

